parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or stranding the driver, and potentially resulting in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: no movement in drive or reverse

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slipping or erratic shifting can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or stranding the driver, and potentially resulting in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The transmission slips or shifts erratically
the vehicle drops into a lower gear
the transmission indicator gives inaccurate readings
the vehicle shifts into the wrong gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission failure with unusual behavior can cause the vehicle to move unexpectedly, leading to accidents or injuries, and potentially resulting in fatalities.
symptoms: The gear shift is out of line
the vehicle backs up when in park
the transmission fails with unusual behavior.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or become difficult to shift, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
The failure of the engine lifters can cause a loud knocking or tapping noise, leading to engine damage and potentially causing the engine to seize or fail.
The failure of the cooling system can cause the engine to overheat, leading to engine damage, seizure, or failure.
The failure of the engine rocker arm shafts can cause engine damage, leading to costly repairs and potentially causing the engine to seize or fail.
The failure of the timing belt can cause the engine to stall or seize, leading to costly repairs and potentially causing accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Failure of Driver's Front Airbag to Deploy in Frontal Collisions
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the driver's front airbag to deploy in a frontal collision can increase the risk of serious injury or death to the driver.
symptoms: The airbag does not deploy in a frontal collision
despite the severity of the impact
and the driver may experience injuries or fatalities as a result.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the electrical system to fail, leading to a loss of power, overheating, and potentially a fire, which can result in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: headlights turning on without being switched on
and loss of power while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities. In some cases, the ABS failure can also cause the brakes to lock up, resulting in a loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: ABS brakes fail to stop the vehicle in a panic situation
ABS brakes cause the vehicle to hydroplane and spin out of control
noisy rear brakes resulting in vibration
ABS malfunction with a blinking noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear axle seal can cause the rear axle to leak fluid, leading to premature wear and potentially causing the axle to fail, which can result in a loss of vehicle control and accidents.
The failure of the automatic transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
The failure of the seat belt buckle can cause the seat belt to fail to latch, which can result in injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Seat belt buckle failed to latch.
